<db:para>To create a blur effect in Qt Quick Effect Maker:</db:para>
<db:orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Add a <db:guilabel>FastBlur</db:guilabel> node to the node tree.</db:para>
</db:listitem>
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Add a <db:guilabel>BlurHelper</db:guilabel> node to the node tree. You need the <db:guilabel>BlurHelper</db:guilabel> node for all effects that contains a blur effect.</db:para>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/blur-effect-nodes.png"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
</db:listitem>
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Select the <db:guilabel>FastBlur</db:guilabel> node and in the settings, change the <db:guilabel>fastBlurAmount</db:guilabel> value to control the amount of blur.</db:para>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/blur-effect-step-1.webp"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
</db:listitem>
</db:orderedlist>
<db:section xml:id="adjusting-item-borders">
<db:title>Adjusting item borders</db:title>
<db:para>The effect appears cropped. You need to adjust item borders:</db:para>
<db:orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Select <db:inlinemediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/effect-item-borders-icon.png"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:inlinemediaobject> to display item borders.</db:para>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/blur-effect-step-2.webp"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
</db:listitem>
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Go to <db:guilabel>Edit</db:guilabel> &gt; <db:guilabel>Project Settings</db:guilabel>.</db:para>
</db:listitem>
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Set the item padding for all sides to 100.</db:para>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/effect-item-padding-dialog.png"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
</db:listitem>
</db:orderedlist>
<db:para>Now, you can see the complete blur effect.</db:para>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/blur-effect-step-3.webp"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
</db:section>
